---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const lastUpdated = '21 May 2026';
const supportEmail = 'support@readlater.app';

/**
 * Plain-English commitments that surface at the top of the page, in
 * the spirit of Readwise's TL;DR and Raindrop's "what we don't do"
 * list. These are not legal language \u2014 the binding policy is in the
 * sections array below.
 */
const promises = [
  'No account. There is nothing for you to sign up to.',
  'No analytics. We do not measure how you use the app.',
  'No advertising. We do not show ads, and we never will.',
  'No tracking. We do not track you across apps or websites.',
  'No selling data. Your library is yours - not a product.',
  'No third-party SDKs. No Stripe, Sentry, Firebase, Google Analytics, Meta or ad networks.',
];

const sections = [
  {
    title: 'Who we are',
    body: `Read Later (the "App") is published by an independent UK-based developer (the "Developer", "we", "us"). If you have any privacy question, write to ${supportEmail}.`,
  },
  {
    title: 'The short version',
    body: `We don\u2019t run a server. We can\u2019t see what you save. Everything you save lives on your device and, optionally, in your own iCloud account. There are no ads, no tracking, no third-party analytics, and no developer-side database of users. The App Store privacy label for Read Later is "Data Not Collected".`,
  },
  {
    title: 'What data the app handles, and where it lives',
    body: `On your device: every URL, title, thumbnail, note, tag and read state you create is stored locally using Apple\u2019s standard frameworks (SwiftData / Core Data), and any secrets are kept in Apple Keychain. In your iCloud (private database): if you are signed in to iCloud, the same content is mirrored between your own Apple devices using Apple\u2019s CloudKit. This is your iCloud container - not ours - and we cannot read or download it. In iCloud shared databases: only if you choose to share a Collection. The people you invite see only that one Collection.`,
  },
  {
    title: 'What we can actually see',
    body: `Effectively nothing about you or your content. The only signals that reach us are: (a) aggregate, anonymised App Store sales and download reports from Apple via App Store Connect; (b) anonymous crash and performance reports, only if you have opted in via iOS Settings \u203a Privacy & Security \u203a Analytics & Improvements \u203a "Share With App Developers"; and (c) any email you choose to send to support. We do not run any custom analytics, ad SDKs, or fingerprinting code.`,
  },
  {
    title: 'No tracking, no advertising',
    body: `Read Later does not track you across apps and websites. We do not request App Tracking Transparency permission because we have nothing to track you with. We do not show advertising, and we do not sell, rent or share your personal information with anyone for any reason. Our business model is paid software, not your attention.`,
  },
  {
    title: 'Fetching the pages you save',
    body: `When you save a link, your device makes a request directly to that website to fetch its title, thumbnail and Open Graph metadata. The request goes from your device to the destination site - we do not proxy or log it. Opening a saved link uses SFSafariViewController, the same in-app browser component used across iOS, which isolates cookies and storage from Safari.`,
  },
  {
    title: 'Purchases and subscriptions',
    body: `Read Later Plus is sold through Apple\u2019s App Store using StoreKit. Apple processes the payment and sends us only an entitlement receipt (a yes / no signal of whether you have access). We never see your name, payment details, billing address or anything else attached to your Apple ID. Subscription, refund and tax handling are governed by the Apple Media Services Terms.`,
  },
  {
    title: 'Subprocessors',
    body: `Because we run no infrastructure, our list of subprocessors is, in practice, just Apple Inc. and Apple Distribution International Ltd. (Ireland) - for App Store distribution, payments, iCloud sync, push notifications and (if you opt in) crash diagnostics. We do not use Stripe, Paddle, RevenueCat, Sentry, Mixpanel, Firebase, Google Analytics, or any advertising network.`,
  },
  {
    title: 'Security',
    body: `On your device, your content is protected by iOS file-level encryption while the device is locked, and secrets are stored in Apple Keychain. In iCloud, your content is encrypted in transit (TLS) and at rest by Apple. If you have Advanced Data Protection enabled on your Apple ID, almost all of your iCloud data - including your Read Later library - is end-to-end encrypted, meaning even Apple cannot read it. We hold no developer-side database of usernames, passwords or content, so there is no central account system that can be breached.`,
  },
  {
    title: 'Children',
    body: `Read Later is rated 4+ on the App Store and is suitable for general audiences. Because we do not collect personal information from anyone, we do not knowingly collect data from children under 16.`,
  },
  {
    title: 'Your rights (UK GDPR, EU GDPR, CCPA)',
    body: `Because we hold no personal data about you, most data-subject requests have nothing for us to act on. You can: export or delete all of your saved content directly inside the App (it is all on your device and in your own iCloud); manage your subscription, payment history and Apple ID data through Apple at any time; and contact us at ${supportEmail} with any privacy question. UK residents may complain to the Information Commissioner\u2019s Office (ICO). EU residents may complain to their local supervisory authority. California residents: we do not sell or share personal information, and we are not a "business" required to honour CCPA opt-outs because we do not process personal information about you.`,
  },
  {
    title: 'International transfers',
    body: `Sync and storage are handled by Apple under their own international transfer arrangements (Apple\u2019s Standard Contractual Clauses, the UK International Data Transfer Addendum, and equivalent mechanisms). Read Later itself does not transfer personal data internationally because it does not process any.`,
  },
  {
    title: 'Changes to this policy',
    body: `If this policy changes in a meaningful way we will update the date at the top of this page and, where the change is material, mention it in the App\u2019s release notes. Continued use of Read Later after a change indicates acceptance of the updated policy.`,
  },
  {
    title: 'Contact',
    body: `Questions about privacy? Email ${supportEmail}. We aim to reply within a couple of working days. A UK postal address is available on request for formal correspondence.`,
  },
];
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy - Read Later"
  description="How Read Later handles your data. No account. No tracking. Your data lives on your device and syncs through your own iCloud."
>
  <section class="relative bg-pouch-ink text-pouch-text">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 sm:px-8 lg:px-10 pt-20 sm:pt-28 pb-24 sm:pb-32">
      <div>
        <p class="reveal-eyebrow text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-pouch-textMuted">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="reveal-lines mt-5 display-section text-[clamp(2.25rem,6vw,5rem)]">
          <span class="reveal-line"><span>Privacy.&nbsp;<span class="text-dim">By default.</span></span></span>
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-5 text-pouch-textDim text-[13.5px]">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      </div>

      <p class="reveal reveal-delay-1 mt-10 text-[17px] leading-[1.6] text-pouch-textSoft">
        This policy explains, in plain language, what Read Later does with your information. The headline is short: it doesn&rsquo;t do much, on purpose.
      </p>

      <div class="reveal reveal-delay-2 mt-12 rounded-[24px] bg-pouch-card ring-soft p-7 sm:p-8">
        <p class="text-[12.5px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-pouch-textMuted">Our promises</p>
        <ul class="mt-5 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-x-8 gap-y-3 text-[15.5px] leading-[1.5] text-pouch-textSoft">
          {promises.map((line) => (
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span aria-hidden="true" class="mt-[0.55rem] inline-block w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-pouch-red shrink-0"></span>
              <span>{line}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-14 sm:mt-20 space-y-12">
        {sections.map((section, i) => (
          <div class={`reveal reveal-delay-${Math.min(i % 5 + 1, 5)}`}>
            <h2 class="text-[12.5px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-pouch-textMuted">{section.title}</h2>
            <p class="mt-4 text-[16.5px] leading-[1.65] text-pouch-textSoft">{section.body}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
